## Additional Information
Note that this change will require updating the `pom.xml` file to use the Jakarta EE API instead of the Java EE API. Specifically, you will need to update the `dependency` block to use the `jakarta.ejb` artifact instead of `javax.ejb`. For example:
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>jakarta.ejb</groupId>
    <artifactId>jakarta.ejb-api</artifactId>
    <version>4.0.0</version>
    <scope>provided</scope>
</dependency>
```
You may also need to update other dependencies and configuration files to use the correct package names and versions for Jakarta EE.
